            "is_prior_year_field": false,
            "draft_value": "* This programmatic request of $9 billion for NASA's Science Mission Directorate (SMD) supports a balanced portfolio of missions across Earth Science, Planetary Science, Astrophysics, Heliophysics, and Biological and Physical Sciences.\n* Funding ensures the U.S. maintains global leadership in space discovery against rising international competition, particularly from China's expanding lunar and deep-space programs.\n* The request provides the budgetary stability required to sustain the specialized aerospace workforce and execute high-priority missions identified by the National Academies' Decadal Surveys.\n* NASA Science delivers outsized returns in national prestige, weather forecasting, and planetary defense while returning approximately $3 to the economy for every dollar invested.",
