            "is_prior_year_field": false,
            "draft_value": "* NASA Science programs invested $4,606,440.94 within the 9th District between FY2023 and FY2025, supporting high-skill research and technical employment at local institutions.\n* Northwestern University is a primary beneficiary, receiving over $6.2 million in cumulative grants for critical research including galaxy formation simulations, astronaut microbial health, and landslide risk prediction.\n* Local partners like Materials Development Inc and Loyola University of Chicago receive funding to advance specialized materials science and astronomical discovery.\n* These investments strengthen the local STEM talent pipeline in Evanston and Chicago, providing students and researchers with opportunities to solve complex technical challenges for the benefit of the nation.",
